Script downloads dump files from wikipedia site.

Usage: 

./bitcoinhits.py YYYY MM DD HH 

All paramters are optional,
if no parameters given, all data available in 2016 retrived by default
CAUTION, one wikipedia gz dump file contains data from one hour,  
processing time is around 1 minute per file
Console output updated on each file.



By specifying additionaly month, day and hour the scope  narrowed to that values

Examples:

   ./bitcoinhits.py 2016 01           # January the 2016, the whole month

   ./bitcoinhits.py 2015 06 29        # July, the 29th 2015, the whole day

   ./bitcoinhits.py 2015 10 10 10     # October the 10th 2015, the 10th hour  (10:00 .. 10:59)



  
OUTPUT SAMPLE:

time ./bitcoinhits.py 2015 02 10 23
2015
Procesing stastics for term Bitcoin in domain en
Getting https://dumps.wikimedia.org/other/pagecounts-raw/2015/2015-02/pagecounts-20150210-230000.gz ... 
Hits in 2015-02-10 during the hour:23 -   339
Grand total:                              339 

real	0m59.325s
user	0m12.229s
sys	0m2.456s




 
